        <p><strong>How can Sustainability be present on a university:</strong>
            sustainability is the concept of maintaining oneself functioning without ever
            ceasing to
            be, this is something that can be applied to pretty much anything including
            universities,
            in a way the can be seen as their own ecosystem and in order for the students
            to survive
            so must the university</p>
        <br />
        <p><strong>What is a sustainable university </strong>: A sustainable university is
            an
            educational institution that educates global citizens for sustainable
            development, it
            provides relevant</strong>
            insights on both social and environmental problems and encourages them to act
            upon such
            responsabilities.</p>
        <br />
        <p><strong>Recycling:</strong> Though this is a obvious one, it is important for the
            topic
            of sustainability, does your university have recycling bins? should they have
            them?</p>
        <p>Nowadays it is very common for universities to have an efficient way for both
            students and
            workers to recycle/get rid of waste. Not only is a good way to keep the
            university/environment clean it also serves as a very good way of
            self-promoting, by making the overall looks of the university more appealing.
        </p>
